##New Year's Eve, write down the "letter of request" Xiaotangshan SARS medical team to assist Wuhan | dialogue

The function introduces, peels off the human shell, records the real sensible life. Presented by the in-depth Reporting Department of the Beijing News.

"We Xiaotangshan team members have sufficient experience in protection, to achieve zero infection of medical staff, can intervene, to help everyone. After the small Tangshan exercise doctor, should step forward, listens to the transfer order. We need to speak out and express our will."

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Guo yabing (fourth from left) and his colleagues before the March. Photo by Xiaoqi Zhou, Hsinking Daily News

By Zhou Xiaoqi, Beijing News

Editor | Xiaoshu Chen, proofread | Lijun Li

This article is about 3308 words long and takes about six minutes to read

On January 23, a letter from the Southern Hospital of Guangzhou circulated on the Internet. It was launched by the former first military medical university southern hospital to Xiaotangshan medical team (Xiaotangshan medical team) . At the end of the letter, they wrote, "If there is a battle, call back, fight and win! " With 24 red handprints and signatures.

This action triggers the demonstration effect, the Southern Hospital asks the war atmosphere to be warm, nearly thousand medical and nursing personnel abandon leave to prepare to return to work at any time. Also triggered many hospitals in Guangdong medical staff to follow suit, give up leave, stick to the post.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The former first military medical university south hospital to Xiaotangshan Medical Team members request letter of challenge. Photo by Xiaoqi Zhou, Hsinking Daily News

On Jan. 24, Guangdong dispatched a team of 135 doctors and nurses to Hubei Province to deal with an outbreak of pneumonia in COVID-19. The team consisted of 42 doctors and 93 nurses from eight hospitals. The medical team will be divided into the medical team for the treatment of common patients and the medical team for the treatment of critical patients.

The 24-MEMBER team from Southern Hospital will fly to Wuhan at 2300 hours on New Year's Eve for support.

At 8 p.m. , they gathered in the parking lot of the southern hospital, where hundreds of colleagues and family members came with flowers to see them off. "My task is to bring everyone safely to Wuhan and back again, " said Guo Yabing, the head of the Wuhan Medical Team, who arrived at the scene after a simple dinner with his family

Before setting out, the team members changed into red volunteer uniforms, affixed stickers on their suitcases that read "Guangdong Southern Hospital Medical Team" , lined up in a row, and shouted the slogan "Go Southern Hospital Medical Team" three times, and boarded a bus to the airport.

Some members of this medical team had supported Beijing Xiaotangshan Hospital in 2003 and participated in the fight against SARS. At that time, medical staff had achieved "zero infection" .

Speaking to reporters from Hsinking, Guo Yabing, the head of the medical team of the Southern Hospital to Wuhan, and professor of the Liver Cancer Center of the Infection Medicine Department of the Southern Hospital, is also the captain of the medical team that went to Xiaotangshan 17 years ago, he told the Beijing News that he had fought against SARS in Xiaotangshan, providing a reference for the COVID-19.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Before setting out, the team members put stickers on their suitcases that read "Guangdong Southern Hospital medical team" . Photo by Xiaoqi Zhou, Hsinking Daily News

"We need to speak out and express our will. "

Peel the onion: Why did you write this invitation?

Guo yabing: a long time ago, when the COVID-19 just found out, our team member Wang Xiaoyan put forward the proposal of writing a petition. Because we found that this epidemic is very similar to SARS. It is similar to the situation in Guangzhou and Beijing at that time. Our team members in Xiaotangshan have sufficient experience in protection. They have achieved zero infection among medical personnel. They can intervene and provide help to everyone. After the small Tangshan exercise doctor, should step forward, listens to the transfer order. We need to speak up and express our will.

You don't have to go to the front, you don't have to go to the front. For example, doctors over 55, older, don't have to go to the front. We want to give people more confidence, to boost their will to fight the disease.

Peeling the onion: After the letter of challenge was issued, did the hospital decide to send you?

Guo yabing: After writing the invitation letter, many of our colleagues have returned their tickets home, return trip, have been ready. The hospital decided today that we leave tonight at 8:00 for 24 people. Related to smoking, infection, cardiovascular, emergency room and other departments are sent, nursing staff will also go, their work is very important, accounting for more than half of the workload.

Xiaotangshan experience: "divided the clean area, semi-polluted area, polluted area"

Peeling onions: How many of you went to Xiaotangshan? What was your state of mind before you went?

Guo yabing: all the doctors, nurses and technicians in various departments, such as inhalation, infection and cardiovascular, make a total of 29 people. The youngest is only 17 years old, and the oldest is 42 years old. Most of them are young and strong.

As infectious disease professionals, it's our job to go to the front. Doctors and nurses, like the general public, can be frightened when they are not familiar with the disease. But after professional training, the understanding of disease is faster than ordinary people, and anxiety can be overcome more quickly.

Peeling onion: How long did you stay in Xiaotangshan? What is the main work done?

Guo yabing: In early May 2003, to the end of June 23, nearly two months. When I left, I didn't know how long I would be staying, and I was still deciding whether to bring my winter clothes, which was actually shorter than I expected. We were in Ward 17, with over 30 beds for patients, and all of the care was taken by our team.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A group photo of medical staff and patients during the Xiaotangshan period. Photo courtesy of the respondents

PEELING ONION: in Xiaotangshan period, the medical team to achieve a "zero infection" , is how to do?

Guo yabing: before going to Xiaotangshan, each leader of the team is to sign a military warrant to ensure that none of the team members are infected. Xiaotangshan very strict protection, there is a strong organizational capacity, discipline, say one thing. Because this is a team, a system problem, no one can drop the ball.

In Xiaotangshan, we have very detailed guidelines, divided into clean areas (administrative and logistics areas) , semi-polluted areas (health care workers living areas) , polluted areas (sick areas) three different areas, we are separated activities.

Like we do infectious diseases born, their professional sensitivity is very high, usually see fever will wear masks, but also developed the habit of hand washing. When you talk to someone, you're used to being upwind, not downwind. Sometimes in the elevator crowded, more crowded, I will hold my breath, to the empty room to breathe again. It's the same for everyone, just to see if you do it right.

Even in the absence of equipment, but also to ensure that the poor, do the critical position of protection, can not wash their hands and rub their eyes. For example, when intubating a patient, the mask suddenly rotted, you can hold your breath for the patient to operate, and then go upwind to catch your breath. It's also good for respiratory isolation.

Peeling an onion: apart from protection, what other experiences can you share in Xiaotangshan?

Guo yabing: sum up a word, it is"the psychology wants to relax, but the protection wants to be in place". Microbial infection is closely related to an individual's immunity. If you have poor rest, anxiety, and immune disorders, you are naturally more susceptible to infection, so we do not advocate fatigue tactics. The medical staff must maintain the confidence, the optimistic condition, can enhance the immunity. When I was in Xiaotangshan, everyone was in a relaxed mood. When we had a meal, we had a meal. We still had to exercise.

The medical core is the medical personnel, must have the fighting strength. It's all about morale. A lot of people lose it when they lose it. In the face of an unknown epidemic, young doctors who have just started to work are panicking and don't know how to protect themselves. We have to tell them how to prevent it. We have to teach them tricks, so that the medical staff can have confidence, and we can't let them get discouraged before they get to work, confidence is everything.

Peeling onion: How are the members of the Xiaotangshan Medical Team?

Guo yabing: The members of the team have become the backbone of various departments of the hospital, such as Wang Xiaoyan, is now head nurse of brain surgery. The youngest player, 34, is a mother. We now have a group, also meet twice a year, we are friends of life and death, feelings or not quite the same.

Team members sign the banner. Photo by Zhou Xiaoqi, Beijing News reporter

Epidemic Prevention and control: "patients must be seen and dealt with when they come"

Peeling onion: You just mentioned, this epidemic is very similar to SARS, what are the main similarities?

Guo yabing: and SARS, Wuhan Pneumonia when it first appeared, we do not know what it is, the way of infection, the source of infection, the severity of infection, how long the epidemic, these are unknown. For example, SARS was only known two months after the outbreak, it is SARS virus, Wuhan pneumonia outbreak less than a month, and soon identified as SARS-like coronavirus.

The first is that the source of the virus is unknown. SARS was not confirmed until 2017. The source is bats. Although the source of this epidemic is also known to be wild animals, it is not known exactly what it is. The second is its infectivity, it can be transmitted from person to person, and at the same time there are cases of infection among medical staff; three, we do not know how long the epidemic will last; four, the places where the virus originated are all one place, SARS is in Guangdong, and this time in Wuhan, outbreaks in other provinces have been linked to people from Wuhan.

PEELING ONION: compared with SARS, this epidemic in the prevention and control of what are the difficulties?

Guo Yabing: from the perspective of Infectious Disease Control, the first is to control the source of infection, SARS symptoms are very clear, fever, cough and other symptoms, it is easy to identify. However, some people in this outbreak have low-grade fever or even no fever. They have some mild illnesses and only consider themselves to be colds. It is difficult to identify them, so it is not easy to control the source of infection. Secondly, the route of transmission must be cut off, this time the virus is spread by air, droplets or mucous membranes on the skin. Wear a mask and wash your hands frequently. Third, develop vaccines and preventive drugs. There are no effective drugs to fight the virus, and no vaccines. Now people are not immune to the new virus, the first wave of exposure to people may have antibodies.

So at present only from the first two aspects to prevent and control, our hospital now set up a separate fever clinic, early diagnosis and treatment, isolation contact personnel, can not run around. Overall, the control of this epidemic is more difficult than SARS, and we are prepared to fight a protracted war.

SHUCKING ONION: Southern Hospital is also the designated hospital of this epidemic, how is the situation now?

Guo yabing: Our hospital has now set up a separate fever clinic, the infection ward has vacated 70 beds, early diagnosis and treatment, isolation contact personnel, can not run around. At the same time, we took people from all over the hospital, many volunteers signed up, finally selected more than 50 people, are young and strong, I gave them the relevant training, the diagnosis and treatment of every link has gone through.

Yesterday morning, I went to the fever clinic to see, there are still 30 or 40 patients in, a heavy burden, these patients must see, see to deal with.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Exterior view of Guangzhou Southern Hospital. Photo by Zhou Xiaoqi, reporter of Beijing News

Peeling an onion: How do you know if a patient has COVID-19?

Guo yabing: according to the guidelines and programs of the Health Commission, one is a clinical diagnosis. Fever outpatient clinic has fever, depending on whether there are cough, respiratory symptoms, etc. ; blood is drawn to see if white blood cells are low; chest film is taken to determine whether there is pneumonia, and then ask about the history of epidemiology, have been to Wuhan, if these conditions are in line with this standard, can be determined as suspected, need isolation. Second, etiological diagnosis, through the kit to suspected patients with samples, to the CDC for two rounds of nucleic acid testing, if both positive, can confirm that the patient has been infected with COVID-19.

Some patients do not have fever and cough. This is called prodromal symptoms, patients may feel weak, or stomach discomfort, will not think of it as a virus infection. After the prodromal symptoms, the typical symptoms, such as fever, cough, and pneumonia, begin immediately. The individual virus is very different, 100 people infected with the same virus, will have different symptoms, so this also makes it difficult to diagnose.
